                        <certainty locus="value" match="../@ref" cert="low"/>
                     </title>
                     <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="1r"/>
                        <title type="incomplete" xml:lang="am" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#Gen">ንጽሕፍ፡ ኁልቈ፡ ትውልድ።</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                        <note>The end, starting from <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>'s reign, is missing.</note>
                        <note>The chapter on <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10245Yared">Yāred</persName>, <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#Yared">Tārika nagaśt: Vita of</ref>, has been omitted.</note>
                        <listBibl type="secondary">
                           <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/KKKATHSD"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1909Listes"/><title level="a">Les listes des rois d’Aksoum</title><title level="j">Journal Asiatique</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Carlo</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Conti Rossini</t:surname></author><date>1909</date><biblScope unit="volume">Dixième Série, 14</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">263-320</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">276</citedRange></bibl>
                        </listBibl>
                     </msItem>
              
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <title type="complete" cert="low" evidence="conjecture" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#Christianization">Tārika nagaśt: On the Christianization in Ethiopia</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                     </msItem>
              
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                        <title type="complete" cert="low" evidence="conjecture" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#ExtractYamaranWag">Tārika nagaśt: Extract of</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                     </msItem>
              
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                        <locus from="11r"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#HistoryDavid">Tārika nagaśt: History of , king of Ethiopia</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                        <incipit xml:lang="am">አጼ፡ ዳዊት፡ በነግሡ፡ ጊዜ፡ ጸላት፡ ጠፋለዎ፡ የኢየሩሳሌምን፡ ሰዎች፡</incipit>
                     </msItem>
              
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5">
                        <locus from="16r"/>
                        <title type="complete">Genealogy and summary of the history of the kings of
                  <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q115">Ethiopia</placeName>, from <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>
                  to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9142TaklaGi">Takla Giyorgis I</persName>
                        </title>
                        <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                        <incipit xml:lang="am">ንጽሕፍ፡ ኁልቈ፡ ተውልድ፡ ጥቂቱት፡ ወለወይዘሮ፡ ትሁን፡ ወነገረ፡ ናሥት፡ እዜህ፡ ይቈይ፡ በድል፡ ነሰር፡
                የተባለው፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡</incipit>
                        
                     </msItem>
              
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.6">
                        <locus from="21r"/>
                        <title type="complete">መጽሐፍ፡ ዘግራኝ፡ ወዘጋላ።</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                        <note>Possibly <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#HistoryGran">Tārika nagaśt: History of</ref> and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2422Tarika#Oromo">Tārika nagaśt: Extract of concerning the</ref>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                
                  </msItem>
              
